  "prompt": "Strike the odd one out and explain your rationale: a) jane austen b) george eliot c) charlotte bronte d) homas hardy?",
  "response": "The odd one out is d) Thomas Hardy.\n\nThe rationale is that Jane Austen, George Eliot, and Charlotte Bronte are all notable authors who are primarily known for their novels that explore social and romantic themes and are typically set in the 19th century. They have a distinct focus on the lives and challenges of women during their times.\n\nThomas Hardy, while also a prolific author of the 19th century, is known for his works that often focus on the issues of rural life and the harsh realities faced by individuals in society. His novels frequently have a tragic tone and explore themes of fate and destiny. Additionally, Hardy's style is more closely associated with naturalism and realism compared to the more character-focused narratives of Austen, Eliot, and Bronte.",
